  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "\nThe SUSE Linux Enterprise Micro 6.0 and Micro 6.1 kernel was updated to fix various security issues\n\nThe following security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2025-54518: x86/CPU/AMD: Prevent improper isolation of shared resources in Zen2's op cache (bsc#1264013).\n- CVE-2026-46300: net: skbuff: propagate shared-frag marker through pskb_copy() (bsc#1265209).\n\nThe following non security issue was fixed:\n\n- io-wq: check that the predecessor is hashed in io_wq_remove_pending() (git-fixes).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
